column5: *** PICS ADDED***  Alright, I dont know if this is going to work so hopefully this pic shows up.  Its my 60" Musky I caught this FALL. I forgot to mention, I am almost 10' tall, thats why it seems so small. You just have to look at it from that perspective    Here are some more pics from this day, Photobucket is now up and running.  As you can see, the day couldnt have been more perfect for being on the water for November 3rd, just not so great for fishing. It was like this all day.
Nice fish but by the size of your hand, I'd put you closer to 11' tall. -Brian
NICE you look atleast 30 inchs across the shoulders and that fish is twice that so I belive ya   ,not much for girth must be a male
Gee Slowpoke... sure glad I saved that picture when I did...

Well I may be close to 11'. I havnt really measured lately.  I just posted this to see if I could post from another board gallery. The OFC gallery wont let me upload cus my files are too big. And I havnt signed up for photobucket yet.  Soon I will get more pics on here. This was just a test for fun
Boy what I would give to have one of those beauties on the line right now! Beauty 'ski!  Man, you must be huge. I guess we'll never go fishing, I only have a 14'er... Even if it is a LUND!
Thats a truly awesome fish!!!!
A 60" OOS ..  ...Looks to be early Spring from your picture or the trees and grass has all died.....  Nice fish.
Nice clean fish but it really does make your hands look big. Thanks for posting.
I think the second photo of it gives a better idea of the size    LOL
Not too shabby, terry
I think there's a real job for Terry out there after all......
Terry...I didnt want to post the original pic. I knew I shouldnt have emailed it to you
Nope, no OOS for me. It was caught Nov. 3rd. 12 days before close.  Give me more credit then that hahaha, I would never target OOS fish.....EVER, but thats just me. I know of too many people that do.
Added some more pics  Enjoy  I will get more on here later
w00t!... man.... is that the line class record? your a giant! LOL  glad to see you posting some pics!  G

I as was little skeptical with that first pic .... close, but just not sure.    That last pic convinced me.   Won't be all that long now until the opener.  Just three looooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooong months.
You did say Summer.....  AGAIN....Nice fish. Credit due.....
Nice Fish Mike,  oh wait thats me
??  Do you make it a habit of saving pictures people post online?
I believe it was an animated picture of a guy stirring a pot, maybe they will post it to show . It was a good one.  nice fish btw
Nice fish... nice pics... especially the close up of the fish head on.
